descript.abstract: The Global Rural-Urban Mapping Project (GRUMP), Beta settlement points consist of estimates of human population for the years 1990, 1995, and 2000 for populated places (points). This dataset is produced by the Columbia University Center for International Earth Science Information Network (CIESIN) in collaboration with the International Food Policy Research Institute (IFPRI), The World Bank, and Centro Internacional de Agricultura Tropical (CIAT)
